  <prompt>GraphClientFactory.cs:90 uses ClientSecretCredential for Graph app-only flows (background jobs, SpeAdminGraphService). Migrate to DefaultAzureCredential so App Service managed identity is used. Eliminates a secret rotation surface.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET engineer.</role>
  <goal>Graph app-only client uses DefaultAzureCredential. No ClientSecretCredential for Graph anywhere.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/GraphClientFactory.cs (line 90 — current ClientSecretCredential)</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/service-principal.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/obo-flow.md (note: OBO flow stays — only app-only changes)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>In GraphClientFactory.cs, replace `new ClientSecretCredential(tenantId, clientId, clientSecret)` with `new DefaultAzureCredential()` (or `new ManagedIdentityCredential()` for explicit MI).</step>
    <step>Verify App Service managed identity has Microsoft Graph permissions: `FileStorageContainer.Selected`, `Files.Read.All`, etc. (whatever app-only scopes the current ClientSecret has).</step>
    <step>Remove `AzureAd:ClientSecret` from any code path that only used it for Graph app-only.</step>
    <step>Build + deploy to dev. Test SpeAdminGraphService operations (admin endpoints).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>GraphClientFactory uses DefaultAzureCredential for app-only.</criterion>
    <criterion>App Service MI has all required Graph permissions.</criterion>
    <criterion>SpeAdminGraphService endpoints work in deployed dev.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
============================================================================
COMPLETED 2026-05-19 — Phase C Wave 2 (parallel with 042 + 049)
============================================================================

PRE-FLIGHT CONTEXT: Task 040 (secret rotation / Key Vault migration) was DEFERRED by
user (dev env, low blast radius). Per the unblock analysis, this task makes 040
substantially moot for Graph: by replacing ClientSecretCredential with
DefaultAzureCredential, the app-only Graph path no longer reads
`AzureAd__ClientSecret` (and never did — it read `API_CLIENT_SECRET`). OBO flow
still uses `API_CLIENT_SECRET` (intentional — OBO cannot use MI).

============================================================================
FILES MODIFIED (3)
============================================================================

1. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/GraphClientFactory.cs
   - Added two new fields: `_managedIdentityEnabled` (bool, default false),
     `_managedIdentityClientId` (string?, optional UAMI client id)
   - Constructor reads `Graph:ManagedIdentity:Enabled` and
     `Graph:ManagedIdentity:ClientId` from IConfiguration directly (same pattern
     as existing TENANT_ID reads — no new DI wiring required)
   - Added startup log line summarizing the chosen auth mode
   - `CreateAppOnlyClient()`: now branches on `_managedIdentityEnabled`:
       * Enabled  → `DefaultAzureCredential` (with optional UAMI clientId pinning)
       * Disabled → `ClientSecretCredential` (legacy local-dev fallback, with
                    improved error message pointing at the MI option)
   - Refreshed class-level + method-level XML docs

2. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.template.json
   - Added a new `Graph` section with `_ManagedIdentity_comment` documenting the
     flag + operator prerequisites
   - `ManagedIdentity.Enabled` defaults to `false` (preserves existing local-dev
     behavior unchanged for environments that haven't opted in)
   - Production should set `Graph__ManagedIdentity__Enabled=true` via App Service
     config / Bicep / Key Vault references — NOT in the template file (the deploy
     substitution pattern handles per-env overrides)

3. projects/spaarke-auth-v2-and-hardening/tasks/041-graph-app-only-to-managed-identity.poml
   - Status: not-started → completed + completion metadata
   - This notes block

NOT MODIFIED (out of scope per task POML "OBO flow stays — only app-only changes"):
   - `GraphClientFactory.CreateOnBehalfOfClientAsync()` and `_cca` —
     OBO still uses `API_CLIENT_SECRET` (cannot use MI; per OAuth OBO spec the
     middle-tier MUST authenticate with a confidential client credential)
   - `Infrastructure/Graph/SpeAdminGraphService.cs` — TWO additional
     `ClientSecretCredential` usages remain (line 3699 in
     `RegisterContainerTypeAsync`, line 3829 in `CreateGraphClient`). These are
     PER-TENANT container-type configs — they use the *customer's* app registration
     secret (fetched from Key Vault per `ContainerTypeConfig.SecretKeyVaultName`),
     NOT the BFF's secret. The BFF's MI cannot impersonate per-customer app
     registrations, so these MUST remain ClientSecretCredential. This is an
     architectural constraint, not a regression.
   - `Configuration/GraphOptions.cs` / `GraphOptionsValidator.cs` — exist as
     dead code (not bound in DI). Left unchanged for minimal scope; future
     work can wire them up if needed.
   - `appsettings.Production.json.template` — only contains logging overrides;
     the production Graph__ManagedIdentity__Enabled flag is set at deploy time
     (App Service config), not in JSON.

============================================================================
AUTH MODE SUMMARY
============================================================================

GraphClientFactory.CreateAppOnlyClient() now supports two modes via flag:

| Mode             | Trigger                                 | Credential                                 |
|------------------|-----------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------|
| ManagedIdentity  | Graph:ManagedIdentity:Enabled = true    | DefaultAzureCredential (+ optional UAMI)   |
| ClientSecret     | Graph:ManagedIdentity:Enabled = false   | ClientSecretCredential (legacy)            |
| (legacy default) | flag absent / unparseable               | ClientSecretCredential (legacy)            |

DefaultAzureCredential chain (when Enabled=true) — devs running locally don't
need code changes:
  EnvironmentCredential → WorkloadIdentityCredential → ManagedIdentityCredential
  → SharedTokenCacheCredential → VisualStudioCredential → AzureCliCredential
  → AzurePowerShellCredential → AzureDeveloperCliCredential → InteractiveBrowser

OBO flow (unchanged):
  Still uses `IConfidentialClientApplication` with API_CLIENT_SECRET — required
  by OAuth OBO spec.

============================================================================
CONFIG KEY IMPACT
============================================================================

Still needed (no change):
  - TENANT_ID, API_APP_ID — needed for `_cca` (OBO ConfidentialClientApplication)
  - API_CLIENT_SECRET — needed for OBO; also fallback when MI flag is off.
    Lots of other services in the BFF (Dataverse, AI, Email, Jobs) also read this
    — see grep results in execution log. Cannot remove from Key Vault yet; out of
    scope for this task.

New (added by this task):
  - Graph__ManagedIdentity__Enabled (bool, optional, default false)
  - Graph__ManagedIdentity__ClientId (string, optional — only for UAMI)

Now obsolete *for Graph app-only* (but still used elsewhere — DO NOT REMOVE
from Key Vault yet):
  - API_CLIENT_SECRET (when Graph__ManagedIdentity__Enabled=true): Graph
    app-only no longer needs it. Other consumers (Dataverse, AI, Email, etc.)
    still do.

NEVER touched by Graph app-only path:
  - AzureAd__ClientSecret: per grep results, only `EmailAssociationService.cs:747`
    reads it. The operator brief's question "is AzureAd__ClientSecret still needed
    for Graph?" — answer: it never was. This task does not change anything for
    AzureAd__ClientSecret. (Task 040's rotation scope is unchanged.)

============================================================================
🚨 OPERATOR ACTION REQUIRED BEFORE DEPLOY
============================================================================

The new MI path will only work if the App Service's managed identity service
principal has the same Microsoft Graph application permissions previously
granted to the BFF app registration. WITHOUT THIS STEP, the deployed code will
authenticate but fail at the Graph API with 403 Insufficient Privileges.

Required permissions to grant to MI Principal ID
`56ae2188-c978-4734-ad16-0bc288973f20` (per operator brief):
  - Microsoft Graph → Application permissions:
      * FileStorageContainer.Selected (SharePoint Embedded)
      * Files.Read.All
      * Files.ReadWrite.All
      * Sites.Read.All / Sites.ReadWrite.All (if used)
      * (any other app-only Graph perms currently granted to the BFF app
         registration `API_APP_ID`)

How to grant (Azure CLI):
  ```
  # Get Graph service principal app id
  GRAPH_SP=$(az ad sp show --id 00000003-0000-0000-c000-000000000000 --query id -o tsv)

  # For each permission, get the role id from Graph SP and grant to MI:
  az rest --method POST \
    --uri "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/servicePrincipals/56ae2188-c978-4734-ad16-0bc288973f20/appRoleAssignments" \
    --headers Content-Type=application/json \
    --body '{
      "principalId": "56ae2188-c978-4734-ad16-0bc288973f20",
      "resourceId": "<GRAPH_SP_ID>",
      "appRoleId": "<APP_ROLE_ID_FOR_PERMISSION>"
    }'
  ```

Then set App Service config:
  `Graph__ManagedIdentity__Enabled = true`
  (and optionally `Graph__ManagedIdentity__ClientId = <UAMI-client-id>` if
   using User-Assigned MI; leave unset for system-assigned)

Restart App Service to pick up the config change (DefaultAzureCredential is
cached in the singleton via Lazy&lt;T&gt;, so the new mode applies on the next
startup).

Defer this Azure-side work to Phase C consolidation (deploy step).

