============================================================================
WHAT WAS DELIBERATELY NOT DONE
============================================================================

- Did NOT modify SpeAdminGraphService (per-tenant container-type configs use
  per-customer secrets — MI cannot replace these; architectural constraint).
- Did NOT wire `GraphOptions` into DI (would require populating
  `Graph:TenantId`/`Graph:ClientId`/`Graph:ClientSecret` which is duplication
  of existing TENANT_ID/API_APP_ID/API_CLIENT_SECRET keys; out of scope and
  would force config changes everywhere). The new MI flag is read directly
  from IConfiguration — same pattern the factory already uses.
- Did NOT remove `API_CLIENT_SECRET` from anywhere — still used by OBO flow
  and many other services.
- Did NOT commit (per operator brief).
- Did NOT rebuild shared libraries (per operator brief — Spaarke.Core /
  Spaarke.Dataverse rebuilt incidentally as transitive deps of Sprk.Bff.Api
  but they were already up to date so no actual rebuild occurred).
- Did NOT touch any directory outside src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ (and the
  task POML itself, which is required by Step 10).
- Did NOT run MSAL browser regression test (per project CLAUDE.md risk-tier
  rule: Phase C is server-only; OBO smoke check at deploy is the right gate).

